// Datasheet for the `io` device — its exposed TYPE (a device's types live in its datasheet, not its
// impl). `file` is a primitive opaque handle for an open file (a raw fd in the opaque cell). The
// operations in io.arche are the only way to act on it; you may move/borrow/return a `file` but not
// write a raw value into it. No storage requirements.
file :: opaque
